All containers/elements for the selected version and action type are shown.
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
-<HattrickData>
<MatchID> : unsigned Integer
The globally unique identifier of the match.
</MatchID>
<SourceSystem> : sourceSystem
Specifies which source system the match belongs to, this replace the old isYouth param
</SourceSystem>
-<HomeTeam>
<HomeTeamID> : Integer
The teamID of the Home team in the match. (Negative for street teams)
</HomeTeamID>
<HomeTeamName> : String
The team name of the Home team in the match.
</HomeTeamName>
</HomeTeam>
-<AwayTeam>
<AwayTeamID> : Integer
The teamID of the Away team in the match. (Negative for street teams)
</AwayTeamID>
<AwayTeamName> : String
The team name of the Away team in the match.
</AwayTeamName>
</AwayTeam>
<MatchType> : MatchTypeID
Integer defining the type of match.
</MatchType>
<MatchContextId> : unsigned Integer
This will be either LeagueLevelUnitId (for League), CupId (Cup, Hattrick Masters, World Cup and U-20 World Cup), LadderId, TournamentId, or 0 for friendly, qualification, single matches and preparation matches.
</MatchContextId>
-<Arena>
<ArenaID> : unsigned Integer
The globally unique arenaID.
</ArenaID>
<ArenaName> : String
The name of the arena.
</ArenaName>
</Arena>
-<Team>
<TeamID> : unsigned Integer
The globally unique teamID.
</TeamID>
<TeamName> : String
The team's full name.
</TeamName>
<ExperienceLevel> : SkillLevel
The aggregated experience level of the team.
</ExperienceLevel>
<StyleOfPlay> : coachModifier
The style of play used in the match. Value will always be 0 for youth matches.
</StyleOfPlay>
-<StartingLineup>
-<Player>
<PlayerID> : unsigned Integer
Globally unique ID of the player.
</PlayerID>
<RoleID> : MatchRoleID
An integer indicating which formal 'slot' (Role) the player has filled in the match.
</RoleID>
<FirstName> : String
The first name of the player.
</FirstName>
<LastName> : String
The last name of the player.
</LastName>
<NickName> : String
The nick name of the player.
</NickName>
<Behaviour> : MatchBehaviourID
An integer indicating the individual order or repositioning that the player has played with. Not provided for Captain and Set Pieces taker.
</Behaviour>
</Player>
</StartingLineup>
-<Substitutions>
-<Substitution>
<TeamID> : unsigned Integer
The globally unique TeamID for which the orders were sent.
</TeamID>
<SubjectPlayerID> : unsigned Integer
If a/ substitution: The player leaving. If b/ behaviour change: The player changing his behaviour. Or c/ position swap: the first player that will change his position.
</SubjectPlayerID>
<ObjectPlayerID> : unsigned Integer
The player entering (or once more the player changing behaviour). Or if position swap, the player to swap with.
</ObjectPlayerID>
<OrderType> : matchOrderTypeID
The type of the order.
</OrderType>
<NewPositionId> : MatchRoleID
An integer representing the new position for the (entering or staying) player.
</NewPositionId>
<NewPositionBehaviour> : MatchBehaviourID
An integer representing the new behaviour for the (entering or staying) player.
</NewPositionBehaviour>
<MatchMinute> : unsigned Integer
An integer indicating in which minute the order was executed.
</MatchMinute>
<MatchPart> : matchPart
Which part of the match the order was executed.
</MatchPart>
</Substitution>
</Substitutions>
-<Lineup>
-<Player>
<PlayerID> : unsigned Integer
The globally unique playerID.
</PlayerID>
<RoleID> : MatchRoleID
An integer indicating which formal 'slot' (Role) the player has filled in the match. All games are 553 based.
</RoleID>
<FirstName> : String
The first name of the player.
</FirstName>
<LastName> : String
The last name of the player.
</LastName>
<NickName> : String
The nick name of the player.
</NickName>
<RatingStars> : Float
The number of stars the player is rated for.
</RatingStars>
<RatingStarsEndOfMatch> : Float
The number of stars the player is rated for at the end of the game. This element is not provided for youth.
</RatingStarsEndOfMatch>
<Behaviour> : MatchBehaviourID
An integer indicating the individual order or repositioning that the player has played with.
</Behaviour>
</Player>
</Lineup>
</Team>
</HattrickData>